    "updated_at": "2017-02-12T22:02:53Z",
    "body": "I mean, IMO the current behavior isn't \"wrong\" in any way, excluding the fact that it is slightly different across platforms.  The events fired make sense and aren't fired at inappropriate places.\r\n\r\nI.e. `restore` does somewhat indicate `show`\r\n\r\nI would rather that we bring windows and linux up to speed with macOS and simply fire show and hide events on minimize and restore.  Semantically it would make sense.\r\n\r\nThoughts?"
  },
